SQL> @ myDBqueries
SQL> 
SQL> --•   1.Identify popular movie genres with respect to age group
SQL> 
SQL> SELECT T1.AGE_CATEGORY,T2.GENRE,T1.TOT
  2  FROM (SELECT AGE_CATEGORY,MAX(TOT) AS TOT FROM (SELECT AGE_CATEGORY,GENRE,COUNT(S1.USERID) AS TOT FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S1,F21_S001_6_MOVIES M1
  3  					 WHERE S1.MOVIEID = M1.MOVIEID
  4  					GROUP BY M1.AGE_CATEGORY,GENRE)
  5  		GROUP BY AGE_CATEGORY) T1,
  6  (SELECT AGE_CATEGORY,GENRE,COUNT(S1.USERID) AS TOT1 FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S1,F21_S001_6_MOVIES M1
  7  					 WHERE S1.MOVIEID = M1.MOVIEID
  8  					GROUP BY M1.AGE_CATEGORY,GENRE) T2
  9  WHERE T1.TOT = T2.TOT1
 10  AND T1.AGE_CATEGORY = T2.AGE_CATEGORY;

SQL> --•2.Identify the most popular membership plan for viewers
SQL> 
SQL> SELECT PLANTYPE FROM F21_S001_6_SUBSCRIPTION_PLAN
  2  WHERE PLANID IN
  3  (SELECT S.PLANID FROM F21_S001_6_SUBSCRIPTION_PLAN S,F21_S001_6_USERS U
  4  WHERE S.PLANID = U.PLANID
  5  GROUP BY U.PLANID
  6  having COUNT(U.USERID) = (SELECT MAX(COUNT(U1.USERID)) FROM F21_S001_6_USERS U1
  7  						     GROUP BY U1.PLANID));

SQL> --3.• Identify movie language preferences of the viewers with respect to location
SQL> 
SQL> SELECT T1.LOCATION,T2.LANGUAGE,T1.TOT
  2  FROM (SELECT LOCATION,MAX(TOT) AS TOT FROM (SELECT DISTINCT M1.LANGUAGE,LOCATION,COUNT(S1.USERID) AS TOT FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S1,F21_S001_6_MOVIES M1
  3  					 WHERE S1.MOVIEID = M1.MOVIEID
  4  					GROUP BY M1.LANGUAGE,LOCATION)
  5  GROUP BY LOCATION) T1,
  6  (SELECT DISTINCT M1.LANGUAGE,LOCATION,COUNT(S1.USERID) AS TOT1 FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S1,F21_S001_6_MOVIES M1
  7  					 WHERE S1.MOVIEID = M1.MOVIEID
  8  					GROUP BY M1.LANGUAGE,LOCATION) T2
  9  WHERE T1.TOT = T2.TOT1
 10  AND T1.LOCATION = T2.LOCATION;

SQL> --4.• Identify most liked movie
SQL> 
SQL> SELECT MOVIEID,MOVIE_NAME FROM F21_S001_6_MOVIES
  2  WHERE MOVIEID IN (SELECT MOVIEID FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY
  3  					     WHERE REVIEW = 'Like'
  4  					     GROUP BY MOVIEID
  5  					     HAVING COUNT(*) = (SELECT MAX(COUNT(*)) FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY
  6  										     WHERE REVIEW = 'Like'
  7  										     GROUP BY MOVIEID));

  2  GROUP BY ROLLUP(ACTIVITY_TYPE,USERID);

SQL> SELECT S.USERID,S.MOVIEID,COUNT(S.USERID) FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S
  2  WHERE S.USERID IN (SELECT USERID FROM F21_S001_6_ACTIVITY_LOG A WHERE A.ACTIVITY_TYPE = 'Watching')
  3  GROUP BY ROLLUP(S.MOVIEID,S.USERID);

  2  WHERE S.USERID IN (SELECT USERID FROM F21_S001_6_ACTIVITY_LOG A WHERE A.ACTIVITY_TYPE = 'Watching')
  3  GROUP BY CUBE(S.MOVIEID,S.USERID);

SQL> --•   1.Identify popular movie genres with respect to age group
SQL> 
SQL> SELECT T1.AGE_CATEGORY,T2.GENRE,T1.TOT
  2  FROM (SELECT AGE_CATEGORY,MAX(TOT) AS TOT FROM (SELECT AGE_CATEGORY,GENRE,COUNT(S1.USERID) AS TOT FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S1,F21_S001_6_MOVIES M1
  3  					 WHERE S1.MOVIEID = M1.MOVIEID
  4  					GROUP BY M1.AGE_CATEGORY,GENRE)
  5  		GROUP BY AGE_CATEGORY) T1,
  6  (SELECT AGE_CATEGORY,GENRE,COUNT(S1.USERID) AS TOT1 FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S1,F21_S001_6_MOVIES M1
  7  					 WHERE S1.MOVIEID = M1.MOVIEID
  8  					GROUP BY M1.AGE_CATEGORY,GENRE) T2
  9  WHERE T1.TOT = T2.TOT1
 10  AND T1.AGE_CATEGORY = T2.AGE_CATEGORY;

SQL> --•2.Identify the most popular membership plan for viewers
SQL> 
SQL> SELECT PLANTYPE FROM F21_S001_6_SUBSCRIPTION_PLAN
  2  WHERE PLANID IN
  3  (SELECT S.PLANID FROM F21_S001_6_SUBSCRIPTION_PLAN S,F21_S001_6_USERS U
  4  WHERE S.PLANID = U.PLANID
  5  GROUP BY U.PLANID
  6  having COUNT(U.USERID) = (SELECT MAX(COUNT(U1.USERID)) FROM F21_S001_6_USERS U1
  7  						     GROUP BY U1.PLANID));

SQL> --3.• Identify movie language preferences of the viewers with respect to location
SQL> 
SQL> SELECT T1.LOCATION,T2.LANGUAGE,T1.TOT
  2  FROM (SELECT LOCATION,MAX(TOT) AS TOT FROM (SELECT DISTINCT M1.LANGUAGE,LOCATION,COUNT(S1.USERID) AS TOT FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S1,F21_S001_6_MOVIES M1
  3  					 WHERE S1.MOVIEID = M1.MOVIEID
  4  					GROUP BY M1.LANGUAGE,LOCATION)
  5  GROUP BY LOCATION) T1,
  6  (SELECT DISTINCT M1.LANGUAGE,LOCATION,COUNT(S1.USERID) AS TOT1 FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S1,F21_S001_6_MOVIES M1
  7  					 WHERE S1.MOVIEID = M1.MOVIEID
  8  					GROUP BY M1.LANGUAGE,LOCATION) T2
  9  WHERE T1.TOT = T2.TOT1
 10  AND T1.LOCATION = T2.LOCATION;

SQL> --4.• Identify most liked movie
SQL> 
SQL> SELECT MOVIEID,MOVIE_NAME FROM F21_S001_6_MOVIES
  2  WHERE MOVIEID IN (SELECT MOVIEID FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY
  3  					     WHERE REVIEW = 'Like'
  4  					     GROUP BY MOVIEID
  5  					     HAVING COUNT(*) = (SELECT MAX(COUNT(*)) FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY
  6  										     WHERE REVIEW = 'Like'
  7  										     GROUP BY MOVIEID));

SQL> SELECT S.USERID,S.MOVIEID,COUNT(S.USERID) FROM F21_S001_6_STREAMING_ACTIVITY S
  2  WHERE S.USERID IN (SELECT USERID FROM F21_S001_6_ACTIVITY_LOG A WHERE A.ACTIVITY_TYPE = 'Watching')
  3  GROUP BY ROLLUP(S.MOVIEID,S.USERID);
